The paper discusses the use of social media and mobile data to collect human behavioral data, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SOC) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of computational methods to analyze and model this data, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper discusses the development of new models of human behavior, which falls under the category of social informatics (cs.SI).
